text.section:
If the merchant or telemarketer is offering real estate, an investment, business, or employment opportunity, the sales presentation shall include the following:
The number of consumers or investors who have participated to date;
The actual experience of the consumers or investors as measured by the standards used in the sales presentations; and
The price of the real estate or investment;
The location of the real estate or investment;
Regarding an investment or business opportunity, the reasonable likelihood of success and a notice of the risk; and
If the opportunity is so recent that no actual performance experience exists, that fact shall be disclosed in all sales presentations, and no other representation of performance shall be made in sales presentations.
